# Lesson 01

# Think Like an Explorer

## Why this lesson exists

Before you choose tools...

Before you install software...

Before you write your first command...

You need something much more important.

A way of thinking.

Technology changes.

The ability to approach unfamiliar problems does not.

This lesson is about becoming the kind of person who can walk into the unknown with curiosity instead of fear.

---

## The Question

How do explorers approach problems they have never seen before?

---

## Learning Objectives

By the end of this lesson you should be able to:

- explain why understanding is more valuable than memorization.
- distinguish between solving a problem and understanding a system.
- recognise curiosity as a technical skill.
- understand why mistakes are part of engineering.
- explain why the Lab exists before any technology is installed.

---

## Understand

Imagine walking into an unfamiliar forest.

You could try to memorise every tree.

Or you could learn how forests work.

Once you understand the ecosystem, every new forest becomes easier to navigate.

IT works the same way.

The goal of the Field Guide is not to memorise technologies.

The goal is to understand the patterns that connect them.

That is why every Adventure asks questions before introducing answers.

---

## Practice

Think about a skill you already know well.

Maybe driving.

Cooking.

Television.

Gardening.

Writing.

Learning another language.

Ask yourself:

- What did I memorise?
- What did I truly understand?
- Which understanding still helps me today?

Write down your observations.

---

## Prepare

Throughout this Adventure you will make mistakes.

Some will be technical.

Some will be conceptual.

Some will simply come from trying something new.

Good.

That means you are exploring.

The Lab you are about to build exists so those mistakes become safe.

---

## Campfire

Before moving on, take a few minutes to reflect.

- What does "understanding" mean to me?
- When did curiosity help me solve a difficult problem?
- What kind of explorer do I want to become?

